The Kwara State Fire Service on Thursday contained an inferno from spreading to other shops located at the Murtala Mohammed road, Ilorin, the state capital. The incident, according to the state fire service, occurred at about 9.43pm and burnt one shop from the 33 shops in a storey building located along the Murtala Mohammed road. Muritala Mohammed road is a business hub in the state capital. The spokesperson for the state fire service, Hassan Adekunle, said the fire destroyed goods worth N542,000 in a shop which was completely destroyed by the fire. Adekunle in a statement said, “The fire burned one shop in a two-storey building comprising about 33 shops in Ilorin on June 2, 2022.  This fire occurred at about 21:43hrs at No. 102, opposite C&S Church, along Muritala Mohammed Way,Ilorin, Kwara State. The incident occurred at about 21:43hrs on June 2 at No. 102, opposite C&S church, along Muritala Mohammed Way, Ilorin, Kwara State. “The leading officer of the crew who attended to the incident announced that they arrived promptly at the scene and were able to limit the damage caused by the ravaging fire to a single shop. The officer further said that the cause of the fire was power surge.’’ Adekunle said that the Director, Kwara State Fire Service, Falade Olumuyiwa, urged residents in the state to be more safety conscious, advising them not to plug devices if they weren’t at their homes, offices or shops to avoid fire disaster.  Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com